Timmy在很长一段时间里都被当作任人摆布的奴隶，通过长期繁重的工作，he已经掌握了各种生产工作的基本技巧，同样，he还磨练出了每个奴才都应有的心态和说话技巧，he不会任性地发脾气，也不会主动和别人发生冲突，卑躬屈膝、强颜欢笑是he人生的常态。

由于Timmy长期进行进行体力活劳作，he显得不怎么受人待见，并且个人形象也不是很好，同样，对于一些需要脑力的工作，he也显得有些吃力。

这个特质通常出现在扩展部分具有神州体力奴隶背景故事的角色身上，也会小概率出现在随机角色上。

races.description: An all-female race of humans spliced with fox genes. Originally, they were Glitterworld designermates from the planet Aolara, but an internal war forced them to leave their homeworld. Now they are spread among the rim.
races.name: Kurin

races.description: Kijins are ogres who were evolved alikes of humans. Their huge bodies and muscles have shrunk, but the muscles are more dense and stronger. They still have to eat a lot to keep themselves up.
races.name: Kijin

races.description:
A tribe of rabbit-like humanoids. They are small and weak, but have powerful legs.
        
        Small bodies leave them roughly 15% weaker in nearly all respects
        Less resistant to cold temperatures
        Over 40% faster running speed
        Generally fine-featured and attractive
        Somewhat Neurotic
races.name: Bun

races.description:
Arachne race lineage can be traced back to Arachne homeworld where the temperature fluctuate between cold and warm.
Arachnes over thousands of generations began to adapt to these temperature and ables themselves to withstand cold but in return have less tolerance to the heat
races.name: arachne

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside.
races.name: Ratkin

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside.
races.name: Ratkin subject

races.description: Goblins are small humanoid beings. With short scrawny bodies and oversized heads with long ears. While physically weaker than an average human goblins have a higher resistance to diseases and toxcicity. What they lack in physical strength they make up with their speed and tenacity. Goblins are fast workers if not the most diligent ones. They're a sly and intellectual race, only hindered by their own greed and violent nature. Goblins exist in primitive tribal structures with constant shifts in power. Often small tribes dominated by the strongest warriors. Both goblin men and women are vicious and both sexes are just as likely to rise to positions of power in a tribe.
races.name: Goblin

races.description: the Marvelous gift of glitterworld bionics. Humanoid with cat ears and tail.
races.name: Nyaron

races.description: Inhabitants of lunar cities that carry the genes of rabbits, the rabbie excel at waging war and constructing mega-cities. They travel the galaxy in search of celestial bodies with planetarium; a drug that the rabbie population has been reliant on for survival since the begining of their history. It is believed they originally came from another galaxy, but have sinced lost the technology and have been cut off from their home galaxy.
races.name: Rabbie

races.description:
A race of humanlike robots which are mostly female in model variety.

The origins of these machines are mostly unknown. Some speculate they are escapees from a civilization which used them for labor and some just suggest they are outdated pleasure machines which got dumped by a passing space freighter.

By design by their previous masters they are weak physically but their raw fortitude is enough to make up for it. Beware of their biological reactor and capacitors violently exploding, if they die by overheating.
races.name: Android

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling around in colonies around the rim which got a resident tinkerer.

Not capable of sapience, however their relative cheap cost and ability to work around the clock make them valuable workers.
races.name: Droid

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike warrior robots.

Usually found guarding the homes of the wealthy and offices of mega corporations. They show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Are traditionally armed with miniguns and core launchers.
races.name: Battle droid

races.description:
A humanoid race living in cities under the sea. Having traits similar to sea creatures, their blood contains substances that can be used for various medical uses.

Descendants of glitterworld explorers who settled in the deep sea, generations of body modifications has led to their current form. Spreading far and wide into the rim, they built many cities and prospered. Until now.
races.name: Moyo

races.description: Lapelli is Developed by advanced genetic engineering. They are strong, strong in strength and stamina, suitable for simple labor, and prefer close combat. They don't care whether they eat raw food or sleep in a cold place or sleep on the floor.
races.name: Lapelli

races.description:
A holographic projection operated by a mind located elsewhere. Despite its humanlike appearance, the avatar could belong to a machine persona with frighteningly alien goals.

If the projection is destroyed, its emitter will need a day to reestablish coherence, but the mind itself suffers no permanent harm.
races.name: hologram

races.description:
Shaggy giants from an arboreal world, the tall and commanding Wookieee species is an impressive sight to even the most jaded spacer. 
        Despite their fearsome and savage countenance, Wookieees are intelligent, sophisticated, loyal and trusting. Loyalty and bravery are near-sacred tenets in Wookieee society. 
        When peaceful, Wookieees are tender and gentle. 
        Their tempers, however, are short; when angered, Wookieees can fly into a berserker rage and will not stop until the object of their distemper is sufficiently destroyed.
races.name: Wookiee

races.description: Togrutas were a carnivorous humanoid species from the planet Shili. The species exhibited head-tails which were similar to those of Twi'leks. Unlike Twi'leks, a Togurta's lekku ran parallel to the head as opposed to behind, making it appear as though they were wearing a headdress. Togruta were also distinguished by montrals, large hollow horn-like projections from the top of their heads, that gave the species a form of passive echolocation. In order to protect themselves from dangerous predators, and to hunt their own prey, Togruta banded together in tribes and relied on their natural pigmentation to disrupt and confuse slow-witted beasts. Togruta worked well in large groups, and individualism was seen as abnormal within their culture, although it was also a necessary quality in leaders.
races.name: Togruta

races.description: Rodians are a reptilian species with antennae, green and scaled skin, large round pupil-less eyes, and snouts from the planet Rodia.
races.name: Rodian

races.description: The Ewoks are sentient furred bipeds native to the moon of Endor.
races.name: Ewok

races.description:
Twi'leks are tall, thin humanoids with skin pigment that spans a rainbow of colors.
      Their most distinctive feature is a pair of prehensile tentacles that grow from the base of their skulls.
      These Lekku are vital to the health of the Twi'lek, which is unfortunate because they prevent the Twi'lek from wearing most forms of head protection.
      Some have theorized that this obvious weakness is why the Twi'lek people have been so heavily targetted by slavers.
races.name: Twi'lek
